description: MEMORANDUM OPINION AND ORDER as to Alexander Mashinsky re: 41 MOTION to Dismiss Count Two of the Indictment, Count Six of the Indictment, and Motion to Strike Surplusage filed by Alexander Mashinsky. The Court has considered all of the arguments of the parties. To the extent not specifically addressed above, the arguments are either moot or without merit. For the foregoing reasons, the defendant's motion to dismiss Counts Two and Six of the Indictment is denied, and the defendant's motion to strike surplusage is denied without prejudice.
